# Audiobook Digitizer

This is a project to create a local UI to digitize your audiobooks on disk.

## Installation

This application requires certain system-level dependencies for processing CD audio.

### Linux (Ubuntu/Debian)

```bash
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install ffmpeg cdparanoia
```

### macOS

Using [Homebrew](https://brew.sh/):
```bash
brew install ffmpeg cdparanoia
```

### Windows
You will need to manually install `ffmpeg` and `cdparanoia` (or equivalent command line CD extraction tools) and ensure they are on your system PATH.

### Python Dependencies

After installing the system tools, install the required python packages:

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

## Running the Application

To start the local web interface, run:

```bash
python app.py
```

Then, open your web browser and navigate to `http://127.0.0.1:5000`.

## Features
- Name a new audiobook
- Interactively rip one disk at a time
- Automatically merge ripped disks into a single MP3 file for easy listening
- View your local library of processed audiobooks